step1:
create a file and name it monitor.sh
step2:
open the file with the Vim editor vi monitor.sh
step3:
paste the script then to make this script executable by running this command
chmod +x monitor.sh
step4:
testing and deployment to run this script
./monitor.sh
step5:
to run this script in the background using the “nohup” command
nohup ./monitor.sh &
